My AccountService Requests










Start, Stop & Transfer ServiceUpgrade ServiceServing Your Shale Oil and Gas LocationHome Warranty CoverageElectrical Surge CoverageMeter Reading ScheduleRequest Letter Of CreditElectric ChoiceRefunds & Security Deposits






Service Requests




Start Service

            To
			start a new service account
             with
            AEP Ohio, be ready to provide:

Your service location
When you want to begin service
Information about you and your account
Billing and service information
A security deposit

Transfer Service

            If you're a current
            AEP Ohio
            customer and you're moving within
            AEP Ohio
            or to another AEP company, you can quickly and easily 
                transfer your service to a new location.
        
Stop Service

Close your account with
            AEP Ohio.
Upgrade Service

            You can modify your electric service
            by:
        

Repositioning your existing meter and/or electric service drop
Removing your existing meter and/or electric service drop
Removing temporary electric service
Removing an outdoor light leased from
                AEP Ohio
Upgrading your electrical service to provide power for a newly-installed electrical
                appliance such as a heating or air conditioning unit

Additional Services

Request Letter of Credit
            Are you looking for credit references? We can send you a letter of credit based
            on your history with us.

Meter Reading Schedule

Learn to read your meter
Track your usage
View your schedule


			Note: Your meter may be read 1 business day before or 1-2 business days after the
			date listed.



Electric Choice
                Learn about customer choice in Ohio.
            


New Construction
            If you're in charge of a building project,
            AEP Ohio
            can give you:

Temporary electric service to the
                building site
Permanent electric service for new premises
Requirements for electrical service




3rd-party Authorization For Business Accounts
		Business account holders can give 3rd parties authorization to access their energy usage information.
	









Are You Moving?



					If you are currently a customer of
					AEP Ohio
					or another company in the American Electric Power system, you can quickly and easily
					transfer your service to a new location.
				



Ohio Customer Handbook

                Get answers to questions about your electric service, including your rights and
                responsibilities as a customer in the AEP Ohio Handbook.










