Careers
At AEP, we hire bright, enthusiastic people with diverse skills, talents, and ideas to serve our more than five million customers
				across 11 states.

				We offer competitive compensation and benefits packages. And, we strive for a safe, healthy, and dynamic work environment
				based on mutual respect for individuals and their contributions.  Read our Mission, Values, & Strategy statements.
			
Application

Want to join our team? Already applied?
CURRENT JOB OPENINGS
LOGIN TO CHECK YOUR STATUS

Note

						The next page you'll see to is not optimized for this device.


Do not show this message again



×



If you are a person with disabilities who needs special assistance with a job application, please call us at 1-877-363-5148.
				State the reason for your call and include the Auto Req ID# found on the Job Details page in your message. We will respond
				between 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. EST, Monday through Friday. All other calls will not be returned.
			
Why Work For AEP?

Pay and Benefits - Employees enjoy competitive compensation and benefits.
Work/Life Programs - Learn about programs designed to ensure work/life balance.
				Message From Our CEO - President and CEO Nick Akins talks about AEP.
Life at AEP - Read what actual employees have to say about working for AEP.

A Diverse Work Culture

Approach to Diversity - We have many initiatives designed to expand awareness about the
					strengths and characteristics of our different cultures.
Military Friendly Employer - We welcome military veterans and have been recognized
					as a top military-friendly employer for many years.

History and Recognition

Our 100-year History - Get a glimpse of our longstanding history as a utility.
Awards We've Won - Read how we've been recognized as a great place to work.

EEO and Harassment Policies

We are an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. For additional information about your EEO rights please review the following links.
					
Read our EEO policy
EEO Supplement
Pay Transparency Nondiscrimination Provision
Read the EEO is the Law Poster


We are committed to providing an intimidation-free, harassment-free work environment.
					
Read our policy prohibiting harassment.



College Students & Recent Graduates

				We recommend JobSTART101: Smart Tips and Real-World Training from
				the Business Roundtable to help you develop the professional skills you need to be successful in your transition from campus
				to workplace. This is made available through AEP's membership on the Business Roundtable.
			





AEP is proud to call itself American Electric Power, and we support our employees who have served or are serving in the military.


 Follow AEP Careers on Facebook to find out about open positions and upcoming job fairs.
                                    








